{"questionId":"13819164","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>François uses the matrix&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd><mtd><mn>7</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>7</mn></mtd><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp;to transform&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;into a new straight line&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>. The object will then travel along&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the vector equation of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd><mtd><mn>7</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>7</mn></mtd><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>λ</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>λ</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>6</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>λ</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>15</mn><mi>λ</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">r</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>λ</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>15</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; (or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for the correct format of a vector equation of a line, <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for the line being completely correct.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13819164","referenceCode":"23N.2.AHL.TZ0.6b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the vector equation of L2.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.11—Vector equation of a line in 2d and 3d"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}